In 1998, the late Kim Jong-il announced a new initiative with the stated aim of turning North Korea into a “strong and prosperous country” by 2012. The project was unveiled in the Rodong Shinmun (the official newspaper of the North Korean Workers’ Party) and the year 2012 was chosen to coincide with the 100th anniversary of the birth of the nation’s founder, Kim Il-sung.
